alert.note: Alert for Carver; Scott; Sibley (Minnesota) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Flood Warning issued May 23 at 10:41AM CDT until May 25 at 7:00PM CDT by NWS Minneapolis
info.description: ...The Flood Warning continues for the following rivers in Minnesota... Minnesota River at Savage affecting Scott, Dakota, Carver and Hennepin Counties. Minnesota River near Jordan affecting Scott, Carver and Sibley Counties. .Rivers have crested and will continue to fall this week. ...FLOOD WARNING NOW IN EFFECT UNTIL THURSDAY EVENING... * WHAT...Minor flooding is occurring and minor flooding is forecast. * WHERE...Minnesota River near Jordan. * WHEN...Until Thursday evening. * IMPACTS...At 26.7 feet, The bridge at Scott County Road 9 and Carver County Road 11/Jonathan Carver Parkway will be closed. * ADDITIONAL DETAILS... - At 945 AM CDT Tuesday, the stage was 26.4 feet. - Recent Activity...The river is continuing to fall. - Forecast...The river is expected to fall below flood stage Thursday morning and continue falling to 20.3 feet Tuesday morning. - Flood stage is 25.0 feet. - Flood History...This crest compares to a previous crest of 26.4 feet on 04/12/2006. &&
info.instruction: Turn around, don`t drown when encountering flooded roads. Most flood deaths occur in vehicles.
